The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 16 March is 242,769 (27,980.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 11 March, there were 7,617 new confirmed cases (877.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 March, there were 4,466 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 71% (3,151 extra cases).
